reviews.text: Small, Welsh Town bustling with local poltury and organic foods.

Narberth is a bustling small market town in the heart of West Wales. There's plenty to do... lots of original shops for clothes, gifts, pottery, ceramics, jewellry... you name it, Narberth has got it. There is a small theatre, a gallery, pubs where local bands play, and restaurants where you can enjoy delicious food of many cultures.
A popular place where locals and tourists alike can enjoy the atmosphere.
